HEADWORD: Statuette
<hw>Stat`u*ette"</hw> <pr>(st⟦acr⟧ch`⟦oomac⟧*⟦ecr⟧t" <it>or</it>
st⟦acr⟧t`⟦usl⟧*⟦ecr⟧t")</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F., cf. It.
<ets>statuetta</ets>.]</ety> <def>A small statue; -- usually applied to
a figure much less than life size, especially when of marble or bronze,
or of plaster or clay as a preparation for the marble or bronze, as
distinguished from a figure in terra cotta or the like. Cf.
<er>Figurine</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Statuminate</ent>⟦br⟧
